 from california’s central coast crimson wine group  about us  leadership crimson wine group top leadership patrick m delong  president and ceo with over  years in wine and luxury brands patrick delong was promoted to president and ceo of crimson wine group in january of  patrick joined crimson wine group in  helping to lead the company’s formation the adoption of its strategic plan and the acquisitions of chamisal vineyards and seghesio family vineyards among other key operational initiatives patrick previously served as the senior vice president  chief financial officer of icon estates the fine wine division of constellation brands inc prior to constellation patrick spent seven years with the robert mondavi corporation in a variety of roles including senior vice president of finance  planning his early career included ten years in operational and financial roles including luxury cruise line holland america line he began his career with deloitte  touche in san francisco patrick is a graduate of california polytechnic state university in san luis obispo with a bs in business administrationfinance  accounting his post graduate studies include seattle university’s masters of applied economics program and the university of michigan’s executive education in strategic planning   craig williams coo  chief winegrower craig williams joined crimson in this role after serving as a member of the company’s board of directors since march  he brings  years of experience in the california wine business including  years at joseph phelps vineyards leaving in  in the position of senior vice president of winegrowing under his direction joseph phelps vineyards earned three point scores from robert parker three top  placements in wine spectator’s top  and the coveted wine of the year award from wine spectator in  for the  joseph phelps insignia williams is also the owner of an eponymous napa valleybased winemaking and viticulture consulting firm craig williams wine company a graduate of the university of california davis he holds a bachelors degree in fermentation science   shannon mclaren  cfo shannon mclaren comes to crimson from wente family estates where she spent four years as the senior corporate controller prior to joining wente shannon served as assistant manager homecare planning  analysis of the clorox company as well as accounting manager corporate segment prior to that shannon served as senior internal auditor of altera corporation before that she served as manager assurance of kpmg she obtained her canadian chartered accountant designation and after being transferred to the bay area in  obtained her california cpa license shannon holds a bachelors degree in business administration with a concentration in accounting from cape breton university in nova scotia   mike cekay  senior vice president of global sales overseeing domestic and international sales for crimson wine group mike cekay joined the company in  with extensive sales management experience globally strong trade marketing skills and a passion for the luxury wine market prior to joining crimson mike was evp and global sales manager for don sebastiani  sons where he delivered  million of gross revenue he began his career as district sales manager for alexander dun  sons – the us duty free division of allied domecq spirits  wine and quickly became allied’s point man on winery relations overseeing a portfolio of over forty wine properties he worked in us cruise ship sales for allied domecq duty free americas and was on premise national account director for allied domecq wines usa dvpcentral region at beam wine estates and vp of offpremise national accounts for future brands llc mike has a bs in marketing from the university of maryland an mba from the university of miami and an ms level  certificate from the court of master sommeliers   nathan stern  vice president of direct to consumer sales nathan comes to crimson from bevmo where he was the head of customer relationship management responsible for developing and implementing an industryleading crm and loyalty programs all direct marketing channels and leading the insights and customer service teams nathans extensive beverage industry experience includes key roles focused on commercial marketing and wine supply at companies including treasury wine estates fosters brewing group coles liquor and altria group inc in addition to his beverage industry experience nathans diverse background includes more than  years in business planning and consulting roles nathan holds a business and law degree from victoria university in melbourne australia   emilie eliason  vice president of marketing emilie eliason joined crimson wine group in  and is responsible for overseeing all aspects of marketing and public relations for crimson wine group most recently emilie was vice president of marketing at j vineyards  winery where she managed marketing public relations and direct to consumer functions emilie has over ten years of extensive brand marketing and direct marketing experience from her roles at treasury wine estates diageo and clorox prior to business school emilie worked in market research analyzing primary and secondary research data to make recommendations for companies such as yahoo gap inc and att emilie has a ba from amherst college and an mba from stanford graduate school of business  crimson wine group  distributors crimson wine group top distributors country  select a country  stateprov  select a stateprov  brand  select a brand  crimson wine group  trade  press  tools  assets  crimson wine group crimson wine group top tools  assets crimson wine group brands crimson wine group pine ridge vineyards chenin blanc  viognier seghesio family vineyards archery summit winery chamisal vineyards double canyon seven hills winery the estates wine room malene luminary forefront brand assets logojpg logopdf photo pat delong president and ceo photo craig williams coo  chief winegrower photo shannon mclaren cfo